03.09.2004
     - This file is now deprecated. All future changes
       to toaster-watcher will be documented in the main
       Mail::Toaster changelog.

01.19.2004
     - Qmail.pm - updated so that rblsmtpd options will
       only be added if rbls are enabled in the config
       file.

12.16.2003 - 1.0
     - Qmail.pm - added code to support fail closed, 
       timeout, and hard failure options of rblsmtpd
     - Added rbl_timeout option to -watcher.conf

11.22.2003 - 0.8
     - Massivly updated Qmail.pm, now we dynamically
       build the smtp, send, and pop3 run files
     - Check to see if we're updating or installing
       the new control file.
     - Added debugging output
     - Only update the file if it's different than the
       installed one.
     - Made changes necessary due to Qmail.pm updates

11.21.2003 - 0.7
      - Moved into Mail::Toaster::Watcher. 
      - Migrated all subs out of toaster-watcher.pl 
        script and into the Mail::Toaster::Qmail 
        module. 
      - Added additional code to also write out qmails 
        pop3 run files based on .conf settings.

11.06.2003 - 0.6
    Updates to the toaster-watcher.conf log file. More config settings were
    added to support the toaster-setup.pl script. It will now read the
    toaster-watcher.conf file and build the toaster per the settings you
    have there.

    Lots more documentation. Added pod sections to script, added
    docs/Changes.pod, FAQ.pod, and Credits.pod. Also published docs to new
    web home for Toaster-Watcher:
    http://www.tnpi.biz/internet/mail/toaster/watcher/

10.06.2003 - 0.5
    Added a bunch of options (and code for them) to work in more diverse
    setups.

    Installs smtp/run file and restarts qmail-smtpd

09.29.2003 - 0.3
    First release - only current function is building the smtp/run file for
    qmail-smtpd.

09.26.2003 - 0.2
    MATT::DNS add to MATT::Bundle

    Polls selected RBL servers via new module MATT::DNS, adds available rbls
    to list for inclusion in smtp/run file.

09.24.2003 - 0.1
    toaster-watcher.conf file format established

